[src:media-source-extensions/addsourcebuffer] The function `getMediaSource()`, which is not defined here, returns a `MediaSource`.
[src:media-source-extensions/api-mediasource] The **`MediaSource`** interface of the Media Source Extensions API represents a source of media data for an `HTMLMediaElement` object.
[src:media-source-extensions/api-mediasource] A `MediaSource` object can be attached to a `HTMLMediaElement` to be played in the user agent.
[src:media-source-extensions/api-mediasource] Constructs and returns a new `MediaSource` object with no associated source buffers.
[src:media-source-extensions/api-mediasource] Returns a `SourceBufferList` object containing a subset of the `SourceBuffer` objects contained within `MediaSource.sourceBuffers` — the list of objects providing the selected video track, enabled audio tracks, and shown/hidden text tracks.
[src:media-source-extensions/api-mediasource] Gets and sets the duration of the current media being presented.
[src:media-source-extensions/api-mediasource] Inside a dedicated worker, returns a `MediaSourceHandle` object, a proxy for the `MediaSource` that can be transferred from the worker back to the main thread and attached to a media element via its `HTMLMediaElement.srcObject` property.
[src:media-source-extensions/api-mediasource] Returns a `SourceBufferList` object containing the list of `SourceBuffer` objects associated with this `MediaSource`.
[src:media-source-extensions/api-mediasource] A boolean; returns `true` if `MediaSource` worker support is implemented, providing a low-latency feature detection mechanism.
[src:media-source-extensions/api-mediasource] Creates a new `SourceBuffer` of the given MIME type and adds it to the `MediaSource.sourceBuffers` list.
[src:media-source-extensions/api-mediasource] Clears a seekable range previously set with a call to `setLiveSeekableRange()`.
[src:media-source-extensions/api-mediasource] Removes the given `SourceBuffer` from the `MediaSource.sourceBuffers` list.
[src:media-source-extensions/api-mediasource] Sets the range that the user can seek to in the media element.
[src:media-source-extensions/api-mediasource] Returns a boolean value indicating whether the current user agent supports the given MIME type — this is, if it can successfully create `SourceBuffer` objects for that MIME type.
[src:media-source-extensions/api-mediasource] Fired when the `MediaSource` instance is not attached to a media element anymore.
[src:media-source-extensions/api-mediasource] Fired when the `MediaSource` instance is still attached to a media element, but `endOfStream()` has been called.
[src:media-source-extensions/api-mediasource] Fired when a media element has opened the `MediaSource` instance and it is ready for data to be appended to the `SourceBuffer` objects in `sourceBuffers`.
